Topic: S3(Simple Storage service) Object Storage:
-------------------------------------------------
-S3 is an object storage service to store and retrive any amount of data at any time from any where on internet.
-Stores objects(files), Ex: PDF files, CSV files, Images, Videos, Folders etc
-S3 is pay-as-you-go
-S3 serverless (no need to manage servers)
-Used for backups, website hosting, media storage etc

Why s3 used?
------------
-Backup and restore: Store import data securely
-Static website hosting: Host HTML, CSS, JS files directly
-Application data storage: Upload user media, documents
-media Streaming: Store images/videos for apps (Ex: Netflix)

Key Concepts:
-------------
-S3 we call bucket 
-S3 bukcet size is 5TB, each account can create 100 buckets
-S3 is like a container where you store objects 

Object:
-------
-File+Metadata (Every Objects has key(name), Version ID, Size(kb,mb,gb) Permission, Data, Data, region

Regions:
-------
Choose where your bucket data physically resides (Ex: us-east-1, ap-south-1)

Naming Rules:
-------------
When you create s3 bucket:
-globally unique 
-No capital, no space, no special characters
-Min characters 3 and maximum character 63

Bucket versioning:
------------------
-Maintains multiple versions of objects
-Prevents accidental deletion/overwrite
-Enable per bucket, not by defualt


S3 Bucket Policy:
-----------------
{
	"Version": "2012-10-17",
	"Statement": [
		{
			"Sid": "PublicReadAccess",
			"Effect": "Allow",
			"Principal": "*",
			"Action": "s3:GetObject",
			"Resource": "arn:aws:s3:::nxgn-demo/*"
		}
	]
}


For Webhosting Example: E-Commerce Application:
-----------------------------------------------
Devopler: Develop application in Java/Python/Node.js etc

Modules of Application:
	-Frontend(I will Host in S3 + Cloud Front + Route 53)
		.login/singup
	-Backend
		.Products
		.Payments (VPC networking+ ECR + ECS + ALB )
	-Database
		.postgress/mysql (RDS)


Aws Services for the above prject:
----------------------------------
.S3 for webhosting
.Cloud front for distribution globally
.Route 53 (domain access www.shiva.com)
.VPC network 
.ECR -Elastic container registry for backend services
.ECS -Elastic container service for backend service
.RDS -For database

additional:
.EC2 server for piplines
.Cloud watch for monitoring
.SNS for notification
.SQS for queing




